summary: Avengers: Endgame - 10 Huge MCU Problems It's Created
title: Avengers: Endgame - 10 Huge MCU Problems It's Created
excerpt: Marvel just played themselves. For more awesome content, check out: http://whatculture.com/ Follow us on Facebook at: https://www.facebook.com/whatculture Ca...
description:
Point 2 is actually pretty concerning. I think we can all agree that a lot of things in the movie, especially the whole time travel deal, were a little, let’s say, not too well thought out. 

But lets put all that aside for a moment and think about this. For five years, the world has gotten used to a drastically reduced population. All of a sudden though, billions of people return. The returned people most likely have none of their previous assets. They can’t just get back to their jobs, they can’t just return to their homes, they likely have no more possessions to call their own, their homes have likely been taken by others or destroyed and after 5 years of adjusting to a certain amount of mouths to be fed in the world, there ISN’T ENOUGH FOOD FOR EVERYONE!

Do you think any of those issues will be addressed in coming Marvel films?

summary:
Can we stop sleeping on how amazing Nat did? 
They couldn’t have won without her sacrificing herself.
And she suffered her whole...
body:
Can we stop sleeping on how amazing Nat did?

They couldn’t have won without her sacrificing herself.

And she suffered her whole life, and when happiness was finally in reach they killed her off. (Can someone link me to the post about that)

Yet, we’re not doing Nat justice to say she was killed off. Because she wasn’t killed off. She sacrificed herself.

She sacrificed herself so Clint wouldn’t have to.

She come so far and she’s grown so much and I just… I love her

summary: It's been an awesome journey, but just like Mr.Stark said, "Part of the journey is the end". Thank you for the best 10 years you...
caption:
It’s been an awesome journey, but just like Mr.Stark said, “Part of the journey is the end”. Thank you for the best 10 years you gave to all Marvel fans, from 2008 Iron Man to the 2019 Endgame. It’s such an astonishing efforts to bring the Marvel Cinematic Universe into reality. For some Marvel fans it’s felt like a loss, watching and having the Endgame as the last installment of the Infinity Saga. Like the words written in the poster in the movie, “Where do we go, now that they’re gone?”, well probably we should wait and hope for the next phase.
“I keep telling everybody they should move on. Some do. But not us.”

See you on the next phase,
I love you 3000
#teamMarvel
